#week-title("Four", "The Long Work as Context & Quarter I Gathering")

=== Core Teaching

The mineral preparations underway — the Via Humida cycles and the Vinegar
of Antimony — will not reach their culmination this month. They will continue
for months and possibly years. This is the nature of mineral work: every
operation is a long work.

The tradition is consistent on this point: "The practitioner who cannot sustain
a preparation without opening it, adjusting it, or abandoning it has not yet
learned the first requirement of the mineral Work." The long work at the mineral
level tests the discipline built across two years more severely than any
previous preparation.

*The long-work mindset at Year Three.* The Adept who has a circulation sealed
from Year Two Month 9, a Via Humida mineral preparation from Year Three Month 2,
and the ongoing Vinegar of Antimony from Month 1 is now tending three distinct
threads of the Work simultaneously, each at its own pace, each requiring
different kinds of attention. This is the living laboratory that Month 8 will
address in full — but the foundation is established here, in the first quarter.

The quarterly discipline of these overlapping works is:
- *Weekly observation* of each active preparation (colour, level, seal, rhythm)
- *Monthly assessment* of whether any preparation has reached a stage requiring
  action (opening, continuing, extending)
- *Quarterly review* at gatherings of all active works, their current states,
  and the practitioner's understanding of where each stands in the alchemical
  process

*Quarter I Gathering preparation.* The student assembles for sharing:
- Their Vinegar of Antimony and first Via Humida mineral preparation
- What it felt like to cross the threshold from vegetable/water work into mineral
- One passage from GCH III that has most illuminated or puzzled them

=== Topics This Week

- The long-work mindset at the mineral level
- Maintaining three concurrent preparations at different timescales
- The weekly-monthly-quarterly observation rhythm
- Preparation for Year Three Quarter I Gathering

#inner-work[
  *Three Works, One Work*

  The three active preparations (circulation, Via Humida, Vinegar) are not
  three separate projects — they are three expressions of a single Work at
  different stages and vibratory levels.

  Journal on how this feels in practice. Is it burdensome (three things to
  tend) or enriching (three windows into the same underlying process)? The
  answer to that question reveals something significant about where the
  practitioner's relationship to the Work currently stands.
]

